<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="35" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="18" pageNumber="35">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="18" pageNumber="35">
Grateloup did not state on how many specimens his description was based; in 
<bibRefCitation author="Grateloup, JPS de" journalOrPublisher="Actes de la Societe linneenne de Bordeaux" pageId="47" pageNumber="64" pagination="389 - 455" refId="B40" refString="Grateloup, JPS de, 1839b. Memoire descriptif sur plusieurs especes de coquilles nouvelles ou peu connus de mollusques exotiques vivants, terrestres, fluviatiles et marins. Actes de la Societe linneenne de Bordeaux 11: 389 - 455" title="Memoire descriptif sur plusieurs especes de coquilles nouvelles ou peu connus de mollusques exotiques vivants, terrestres, fluviatiles et marins." volume="11" year="1839 b">Grateloup (1839b</bibRefCitation>
: 420) he gave as measurements &quot;Hauteur: 80 mill. - 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Diamètre">Diametre</normalizedToken>
: 35 Mill.&quot; and said it was from &quot;Mon cabinet&quot;. As 
<bibRefCitation author="Breure, ASH" journalOrPublisher="Zoologische Verhandelingen Leiden" pageId="45" pageNumber="62" pagination="1 - 255" refId="B9" refString="Breure, ASH, 1978. Notes on and descriptions of Bulimulidae (Mollusca, Gastropoda). Zoologische Verhandelingen Leiden 164: 1 - 255" title="Notes on and descriptions of Bulimulidae (Mollusca, Gastropoda)." volume="164" year="1978">Breure (1978)</bibRefCitation>
noted, this specimen &quot;From Grateloup Colln.&quot; came to the NHMUK collection via da Costa, who purchased the specimen from the dealers Sowerby and Fulton. 
<bibRefCitation author="Reeve, LA" journalOrPublisher="Reeve, Benham and Reeve, London" pageId="51" pageNumber="68" refId="B106" refString="Reeve, LA, 1848-1850. Conchologica iconica or illustrations of the shells of molluscous animals, 5. Bulimus. Reeve, Benham and Reeve, London" title="Conchologica iconica or illustrations of the shells of molluscous animals, 5. Bulimus" year="1848 - 1850">Reeve (1848 [1848-1850])</bibRefCitation>
evidently based his description on a different specimen, as he wrote &quot;The shell named 
<taxonomicName authority="Scopoli, 1777" authorityName="Grateloup" authorityYear="1839" class="Gastropoda" family="Bulimulidae" genus="Bulimus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bulimus magnificus" order="Pulmonata" pageId="18" pageNumber="35" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="magnificus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="35">Bulimus magnificus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by M. Grateloup is, according to the specimen so marked in Mr. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Cuming’s">Cuming's</normalizedToken>
collection, a variety of 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="35">Bulimus Taunaysii</emphasis>
[supposed by Reeve to be 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Férussac’s">Ferussac's</normalizedToken>
species] of a lighter brown colour&quot;. Despite the confusing localities (
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Brésil”">&quot;Bresil&quot;</normalizedToken>
seems to be added in a later hand), the status of this specimen is not disputed herein; the Peruvian locality, however, still needs confirmation. The current systematic position follows 
<bibRefCitation author="Simone, LRL" journalOrPublisher="EGB / Fapesp, Sao Paulo" pageId="52" pageNumber="69" refId="B121" refString="Simone, LRL, 2006. Land and freshwater molluscs of Brazil. EGB/Fapesp, Sao Paulo" title="Land and freshwater molluscs of Brazil." year="2006">Simone (2006)</bibRefCitation>
, who reported this species from the states of Rio de Janeiro and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="São">Sao</normalizedToken>
Paulo.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
